A question: Refreshing my knowledge with the [config spec](https://specs.opencontainers.org/image-spec/config/?v=v1.0.1), I see that the config object has a `Labels` field intended to capture "... arbitrary metadata for the container."  Then, the config object, being a [descriptor](https://specs.opencontainers.org/image-spec/descriptor/?v=v1.0.1) (if I'm understanding correctly), can also be assigned generic [annotations](https://specs.opencontainers.org/image-spec/annotations/).  Which would we want to utilize here?

(As an aside, I built on this PR to play around a bit and I'm not immediately seeing generic annotations added to the config layer ([here](https://github.com/fermyon/spin/blob/main/crates/oci/src/client.rs#L189)) show up as intended in the manifest json... so there may be a bit of further work either in our oci client or the underlying [oci-distribution](https://github.com/fermyon/oci-distribution) crate.  I haven't yet tried adding metadata to the `Config.Labels` object on the config...)
